y, $1.36%; October. $1.28%.\nNEWYOKK STOCKS.\nElectric Boat 14%\nFisk Rubber 17\nGen. Outdoor Adv 40%\nHupp 21%\nM. K. and T., pfd 97%\nMo. Pacific pfd 97%\nMack Truck 94_\nNorth American 47%\nNash Motor 66%\nPackard Motor 35%\nR. J. Reynolds B 122%\nWoolworth 127\nMidwest Utilities 112%\nFriday\u2019s Grain Changes\nBarley\u2014Slow; unchanged.\nCorn\u2014l@ 2c higher.\nOats \u2014Unchanged.\nRye\u2014Firm.\nWheat \u2014Unchanged.\nBILLION-DOLLAR\nRAIL MERGER\nUP TO I. 0.0.\nWASHINGTON\u2014The Van Swer\ningen billion-dolla> rail merger,\nonce turned down by the interstate\ncommerce commission, came to the\nfront in a new form yesterday when\nthe Chesapeake Ohio railroad ai>-\nplied to the interstate commerce\ncommission for authority to control\nthe Erie and Pere Marquette lines\nthrough stock ownership.\nBoth roads were to have been in\ncluded in the billion-dollar merger.\nAt the same time the Chesapeake\nOhio petitioned the interstate\ncommerce commission for authority\nto issue additional common shares\nof C. O. stock to the value of\n$59,502,000 par.\nWould Buy Shares.\nThe application of the Chesa\npeake Ohio set forth in detail the\nmethod by which it is proposed, to\nacquire stock control of the Erie\nand Pere Marquette.\nIn addition to the shares now\nowned outright the Chesapeake\nOhio will purchase, subject to the\ncommission\u2019s approval, shared of\nthe Erie Pere Marquette covered\nin options obtained from O. P. Van\nSweringen. It will acquire from the\nNickel Pate 174,900 shares of Pere\nMarquette common now under con\ntract. Such additional shares of\nPere Marquette will be purchasy\nin order to give the Chesapeake\nOhio numerical majority of the\ncommon stock in both roads.\nNew Basis For System.\nA special commission represent\ning the Chesapeake Ohio fixed a\nprice on all Erie shares covered in\nthe Van Sweringen options ar $34.50\na share on 345,239 shares of com\nmon; a fraction over $45,87 on 23.-\nG 95 shares of first preferred, and\n$43.75 for 22,305 shares of second\npreferred. These shares at these\nprices aggregate $3,348,350 less than\nthe market value at tne close of the\nmarket, Jan. 31.\nThe practical effect of the new\nVan Sweringen plan is\u2019to make the\nChesapeake Ohio, Instead of the\nNickel Plate, the basis for the great,\nsystem which the two brothers have\nprojected.\nTreasury Statement\nWASHINGTON\u2014The following is a\nstatement of the condition of the United\nStates treasury on Feb. 9:\nIncome to date this year. .$2,259,365,404\nIncome to date last year.. 2,170,406.384\nIncrease 78,959,020\nIncome over outgo this years 72,990,935\nIncome over outgo last year 90,309,511\nDecrease 17,318,576\nBalance gen. fund today..! 175,676,545\nBalance previous day 179,301,323\nDecrease 3,624,763\nChicago Produce\nCHICAGO Butter\u2014Receipts, 4,898;\ncreameries, 48%@49c; standards, 49%e;\nfirsts, 46%@47%c; seconds, 44@4 5% c;\nextras, 49 %c. Eggs\u2014Receipts, 9,340;\nordinaries, 32c; firsts, 33c. Cheese\nTwins, 25@25%c; Young Americas, 26c.\nPoultry'\u2014Receipts, six cars; fowls,\nheavy, 25c; email, 22c; springs, 28c;\nducks, heavy, 32c; geese, 23c; turkeys\nNo. 1. 30c; roosters, 20c. Potatoes \u2014Ar-\nrivals, 5 4cars; on track, 193; in transit,\n737; Wisconsin sacked round whites No.\n1, $1.90@2,10, mostly around $2.00;\npartly graded, $1.70@1.90; Idaho sacked\nrussets No. 1, $2.6b@2.85, mostly $2.70@\n2.75; commercial pack, $2.40@2.60\nSweet potatoes\u2014sl.7s @2.00.\nChicago Livestock\nCHICAGO Cattle\u2014Receipts, 3,006;\nmost killing classes steady to strong;\nbulls slow, weak; fat steers scarce; best\nat $11.75; few loads $11.00@11.50; bulk,_\n$9.00@10.50; weighty Texas cake, $10.50;\u201d\nlighter and less desirable kinds, $9.50@\n9.75; .stockers and feeders firm, $7.25@\n8.25; most medium bulls, $6.00@625;\nvealers, $12,50 @13.50; outsiders up to\n$15.50.\nSheep\u2014Receipts, 14,000; market very\nslow; few early sales fat lambs about\nsteady; top to shippers, $13.25; desirable